    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.27-29_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">27</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        225 Willard Way, Ithaca <hi rend="caps">NY</hi>
                            Jan 26, 1959
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John: &#821;</salute></opener> <p>I came in late this afternoon to find both your letter and the record here. Nita had gone to Syracuse with a friend. So I had to get my supper. As soon as I had finished, I read your letter and rejoiced in the gifts and tributes that have come to you following the close of your <hi rend="caps">T.V.</hi> series: Then I played the whole of the record. It is <hi rend="underline">beautiful.</hi> I had no trouble at all with the connections between the excerpts. True, I know the poem. But with just a little thinking any hearer should get the connections.</p>
                
                <p>Your voice was (and still <hi rend="underline">is</hi>) so <hi rend="underline">good</hi>. And how your spoken words and emphases made the story come alive. I think that never before had I fully sensed the terrific scene of that prairie fire. I could almost see the
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.27-29_0002"/>
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">28</fw>
                
                    leaping flames, the back cloud above, the maddened rush of all animal <del/> life before the terror.</p>
                
                <p>Thank you so much dear friend for that gift which whenever I <unclear>use it</unclear> will seem to bring you into the room. And how thoughtful of you to autograph it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Slade</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>With your voice speaking, I could note the things you emphasize because you believe in them so deeply &#8212; this, for example, . . .</p>
                    <lg>
                        <l>"All he</l>
                        <l>hath</l>        
                        <l>A Man will give for life! But shall he give</l>
                        <l>For living that which makes it good to live &#8212;"</l>
                    </lg>
                    <p>Surely poetry is a vocal art</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
